WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.475 --> 00:00:12.614
It is sad. but you've
picked a wonderful place to die.

2
00:00:12.747 --> 00:00:14.114
This is the library.

3
00:00:14.248 --> 00:00:16.350
There are many fine works
of literature to peruse.

4
00:00:16.483 --> 00:00:18.151
but of course we are limited

5
00:00:18.285 --> 00:00:20.822
to whatever
the Livings are perusing

6
00:00:20.955 --> 00:00:22.824
because of our inability

7
00:00:22.957 --> 00:00:25.058
to interact with
the physical world.

8
00:00:26.528 --> 00:00:28.696
Yeah. this being a ghost thing
is wild.

9
00:00:28.830 --> 00:00:30.532
Oh. and that big Viking guy

10
00:00:30.665 --> 00:00:32.534
was telling me something about
ghost powers.

11
00:00:32.667 --> 00:00:34.334
Do you have one of those?

12
00:00:36.671 --> 00:00:38.205
No.

13
00:00:38.338 --> 00:00:39.473
There she is.

14
00:00:39.607 --> 00:00:40.708
So it's true.

15
00:00:40.842 --> 00:00:42.544
Um. hello.

16
00:00:42.677 --> 00:00:45.479
I'm Nigel.
and this is Creepy Dirk.

17
00:00:45.613 --> 00:00:47.015
We live in the basement.

18
00:00:47.147 --> 00:00:49.551
We're kind of the social elite
of the house.

19
00:00:49.684 --> 00:00:53.053
So. are you dating anyone yet?

20
00:00:53.186 --> 00:00:54.421
I died two days ago.

21
00:00:54.556 --> 00:00:56.323
There's always
a bit of a feeding frenzy

22
00:00:56.456 --> 00:00:58.058
when a new ghost arrives.

23
00:00:58.191 --> 00:01:02.062
Welcome. I'm Baxter. of
the Revolutionary shed ghosts.

24
00:01:02.195 --> 00:01:04.231
I hear you're a musician.

25
00:01:04.364 --> 00:01:05.900
Which is something
we have in common.

26
00:01:06.034 --> 00:01:08.036
I play the fife.

27
00:01:08.168 --> 00:01:09.336
Oh. that's nice.

28
00:01:09.469 --> 00:01:10.772
Okay. well.

29
00:01:10.905 --> 00:01:13.407
now the competition's grown
too intense.

30
00:01:13.541 --> 00:01:16.176
So it would be pointless for me
to throw my hat into the ring

31
00:01:16.310 --> 00:01:18.746
at this late date.

32
00:01:18.880 --> 00:01:20.548
Darn! Darn!

33
00:01:20.682 --> 00:01:23.551
Anyway. may the best man win.

34
00:01:25.720 --> 00:01:27.087
Isn't he...

35
00:01:27.220 --> 00:01:29.222
-Oh. yeah.
-Big-time.
-Very much so.

36
00:01:34.361 --> 00:01:36.430
Jay. we're helping Trevor
brainstorm

37
00:01:36.564 --> 00:01:38.533
some gift ideas for his boss.

38
00:01:38.666 --> 00:01:40.602
If you were turning 50.
what would you want?

39
00:01:40.735 --> 00:01:42.102
Batman action figure.

40
00:01:42.235 --> 00:01:44.572
specifically
the 1966 Marx Bendable Batman.

41
00:01:44.706 --> 00:01:46.206
Did it shrivel
your desire for him.

42
00:01:46.340 --> 00:01:48.108
how quickly he came up
with that?

43
00:01:48.241 --> 00:01:50.110
Okay. you don't ask nerd boy
for help picking out a gift

44
00:01:50.243 --> 00:01:52.112
for a finance baller like Brett.

45
00:01:52.245 --> 00:01:54.281
I need to get this right.

46
00:01:54.414 --> 00:01:55.617
The pressure is on.

47
00:01:55.750 --> 00:01:57.652
This is for my boss!

48
00:01:57.785 --> 00:02:00.120
Gifts are tricky.
particularly for your superiors.

49
00:02:00.253 --> 00:02:02.255
One time. a butler gifted me
a silk scarf.

50
00:02:02.389 --> 00:02:04.926
and it actually earned him
a pay cut.

51
00:02:05.059 --> 00:02:07.260
He should not be able
to afford a silk scarf.

52
00:02:07.394 --> 00:02:09.631
Exactly. You don't want
to come on too strong.

53
00:02:09.764 --> 00:02:11.799
or you'll be perceived
as a kiss-ass.

54
00:02:11.933 --> 00:02:13.635
But you can't go too cheap.

55
00:02:13.768 --> 00:02:15.770
like when Sam got Jay's mom
that beer cozy.

56
00:02:17.572 --> 00:02:19.473
That was supposed to be ironic.

57
00:02:19.607 --> 00:02:21.241
Because she drinks tea.

58
00:02:21.375 --> 00:02:23.978
Oh. so the joke is that
it's useless to her. Good one.

59
00:02:24.112 --> 00:02:26.313
Ooh! What about a jaguar?

60
00:02:26.446 --> 00:02:28.950
I think a car is
coming on too strong.

61
00:02:29.083 --> 00:02:31.519
What? No. I'm talking
about the animal.

62
00:02:31.653 --> 00:02:35.023
Once trained.
jaguars make excellent pets.

63
00:02:35.155 --> 00:02:37.457
Though not
for the postal carrier.

64
00:02:37.592 --> 00:02:39.661
Your jaguar attacked
your mailman?

65
00:02:39.794 --> 00:02:41.194
Okay. that's got to be Hetty.

66
00:02:41.328 --> 00:02:43.665
Let me guess:
They're also delicious to eat.

67
00:02:43.798 --> 00:02:47.101
A little gamy. actually.
for my taste.

68
00:02:47.234 --> 00:02:50.605
But their skulls make
handsome cocaine bowls.

69
00:02:50.738 --> 00:02:52.140
Maybe one of those.

70
00:02:52.272 --> 00:02:54.142
It's not too expensive.
and-and it's thoughtful.

71
00:02:54.274 --> 00:02:56.176
given what you've said
about your boss's predilections.

72
00:02:56.309 --> 00:02:58.345
Yeah. sure.
Sam. can you run over to Target.

73
00:02:58.478 --> 00:03:00.515
see if they have
any jaguar skull cocaine bowls

74
00:03:00.648 --> 00:03:02.050
left in stock?

75
00:03:02.182 --> 00:03:05.352
See? This discussion
was fruitful after all.

76
00:03:05.485 --> 00:03:07.055
What you doing?

77
00:03:07.187 --> 00:03:08.956
I'm waiting for Pete
to get back.

78
00:03:09.090 --> 00:03:11.693
He went to Jamaica to see if
any of my relatives are ghosts.

79
00:03:11.826 --> 00:03:14.862
Pete also cross ocean for Thor.
but much further.

80
00:03:14.996 --> 00:03:16.631
Greater risk he disappear.

81
00:03:16.764 --> 00:03:19.199
-What's your point?
-Just that Thor special. too.

82
00:03:19.332 --> 00:03:20.367
Okay.

83
00:03:20.501 --> 00:03:22.469
Howdy!

84
00:03:22.603 --> 00:03:25.039
Uhp. pardon me. I'm a little
shorthanded.

85
00:03:25.173 --> 00:03:26.641
Oh. Pete. you're back!

86
00:03:26.774 --> 00:03:28.976
Glad you back from Jamaica.

87
00:03:29.110 --> 00:03:30.377
- which is much closer
than Norway.

88
00:03:30.511 --> 00:03:31.979
So. tell me everything.

89
00:03:32.113 --> 00:03:34.682
How was your trip?
Did you locate any of my family?

90
00:03:34.816 --> 00:03:36.150
As a matter of fact. I did.

91
00:03:36.283 --> 00:03:37.919
Your grandmother. Hortense.
is a ghost.

92
00:03:38.052 --> 00:03:39.854
-Oh. my God. You talked to her?
-Yep.

93
00:03:39.987 --> 00:03:41.689
She is a peach of a lady.

94
00:03:41.823 --> 00:03:44.058
And she has a message for you.
Do you want me to do her accent?

95
00:03:44.192 --> 00:03:45.827
-No.
-Copy that.

96
00:03:45.960 --> 00:03:47.829
Well. she was thrilled to learn
that you're a singer.

97
00:03:47.962 --> 00:03:49.697
She still remembers you
as a three-year-old

98
00:03:49.831 --> 00:03:52.567
belting out spirituals
on a summer Sunday.

99
00:03:52.700 --> 00:03:54.869
Alberta. she was just beaming
with pride about you.

100
00:03:55.002 --> 00:03:57.572
I'm touched that you would
do this for me.

101
00:03:57.705 --> 00:04:00.074
-Honestly. I'm getting
a little choked up.
-Aw. yeah.

102
00:04:00.208 --> 00:04:01.843
Donna thought
you might react that way.

103
00:04:01.976 --> 00:04:04.579
I'm sorry. what? You saw Donna?

104
00:04:04.712 --> 00:04:06.748
Your ex-girlfriend Donna?

105
00:04:06.881 --> 00:04:07.949
Yeah. yeah.
I was in the neighborhood.

106
00:04:08.082 --> 00:04:09.217
so I thought. "Why not?"

107
00:04:09.349 --> 00:04:11.284
Yeah. Why not?

108
00:04:11.418 --> 00:04:13.721
Because they used to
have intercourse.

109
00:04:13.855 --> 00:04:15.923
-Could be awkward.
-Oh. come on.

110
00:04:16.057 --> 00:04:18.226
We're just friends.
It's not awkward at all.

111
00:04:18.358 --> 00:04:19.761
If you say so.

112
00:04:19.894 --> 00:04:22.864
Uh. Sam? We got to talk.

113
00:04:22.997 --> 00:04:25.398
Oh. Trevor just came in
looking concerned.

114
00:04:25.533 --> 00:04:27.869
Well. I settled on a
birthday gift for my boss Brett.

115
00:04:28.002 --> 00:04:30.437
and it did not go over
how I'd hoped.

116
00:04:30.571 --> 00:04:32.807
-What'd you get him?
-It's called a stripper-gram.

117
00:04:32.940 --> 00:04:34.307
Oh. my God.

118
00:04:34.441 --> 00:04:36.611
Trevor got Brett a stripper-gram
for his birthday.

119
00:04:36.744 --> 00:04:39.947
The Brettinator?
I bet he loved that. right?

120
00:04:40.081 --> 00:04:43.084
He did. It's just.
Human Resources did not.

121
00:04:43.217 --> 00:04:46.453
Okay. I'm taking from context
clues that a stripper-gram

122
00:04:46.587 --> 00:04:48.156
is like a telegram.

123
00:04:48.288 --> 00:04:50.558
but the message is delivered
by some sort of harlot.

124
00:04:50.691 --> 00:04:52.560
She was dressed
as an HVAC repairwoman.

125
00:04:52.693 --> 00:04:55.395
The bit being that she felt
it was so hot in Brett's office

126
00:04:55.530 --> 00:04:57.397
that she could not perform
her duties clothed.

127
00:04:57.532 --> 00:04:59.000
Forget the stripping.
I'm hooked on the plot.

128
00:04:59.133 --> 00:05:01.836
Apparently. stupid Linda
from accounting happened by.

129
00:05:01.969 --> 00:05:03.805
reported the whole thing.

130
00:05:03.938 --> 00:05:06.473
Didn't even let Candi
get to the big finish.

131
00:05:06.607 --> 00:05:08.843
So what does this mean?
Are you fired?

132
00:05:08.976 --> 00:05:11.012
Not exactly. but it's bad.

133
00:05:11.145 --> 00:05:13.981
HR wants to see me tomorrow.
in person.

134
00:05:14.115 --> 00:05:15.583
But you can't go in person.

135
00:05:15.716 --> 00:05:17.685
And even if you could.
they could not see you.

136
00:05:17.819 --> 00:05:21.321
HR wants to see Trevor tomorrow.
in New York. in person.

137
00:05:21.454 --> 00:05:22.824
Okay.

138
00:05:22.957 --> 00:05:24.692
This is simple.

139
00:05:24.826 --> 00:05:27.662
Young Jay must simply redon
his persona of Michael Jackson.

140
00:05:27.795 --> 00:05:30.497
which he did so successfully at
the work retreat at Woodstone.

141
00:05:30.631 --> 00:05:32.700
and head into the city
in Trevor's stead.

142
00:05:32.834 --> 00:05:33.968
The ghosts are saying...

143
00:05:34.101 --> 00:05:35.670
I know what they're saying. Sam.

144
00:05:35.803 --> 00:05:38.840
They want me to get chewed out
by HR on Trevor's behalf.

145
00:05:38.973 --> 00:05:40.007
Well. guess what.

146
00:05:40.141 --> 00:05:41.976
I'm not doing it!

147
00:05:42.109 --> 00:05:43.177
Uh. Jay...

148
00:05:43.311 --> 00:05:45.213
No. don't "Jay" me. okay?

149
00:05:45.345 --> 00:05:46.681
It's a nonstarter.

150
00:05:46.814 --> 00:05:48.616
What do I care
if a ghost lost their job?

151
00:05:48.749 --> 00:05:51.285
Frankly. I think it's weird
that a ghost has a job at all.

152
00:05:51.451 --> 00:05:53.654
and I don't think
that's a controversial opinion!

153
00:05:53.788 --> 00:05:55.690
Are you gonna tell him
or should I. Sam?

154
00:05:55.823 --> 00:05:59.359
The thing is. we're sort of--
how do I put this?--

155
00:05:59.492 --> 00:06:02.029
uh. dependent on Trevor's salary

156
00:06:02.163 --> 00:06:04.031
to stay financially solvent.

157
00:06:04.165 --> 00:06:06.133
Excuse me?

158
00:06:06.267 --> 00:06:08.870
It's just. we've encountered
so many unexpected expenses.

159
00:06:09.003 --> 00:06:10.671
and I tried to make
the numbers work.

160
00:06:10.805 --> 00:06:12.206
but the math
wasn't mathing. Jay.

161
00:06:12.340 --> 00:06:14.508
So No Pants has been
keeping us afloat?

162
00:06:14.642 --> 00:06:16.878
Ironic for a guy who was fished
out of the bottom of a lake.

163
00:06:17.011 --> 00:06:18.346
I wanted to tell you.

164
00:06:18.478 --> 00:06:20.882
but I also didn't want
to stress you out.

165
00:06:21.015 --> 00:06:22.415
You've been working so hard.

166
00:06:22.550 --> 00:06:24.151
trying to get the restaurant
up and running.

167
00:06:24.285 --> 00:06:26.320
But what about the list?
We-we got on the list.

168
00:06:26.453 --> 00:06:28.522
And it's helping some.
We're getting busier.

169
00:06:28.656 --> 00:06:31.058
and that's great momentum
that we need to build on.

170
00:06:31.192 --> 00:06:33.227
But we're not profitable yet.

171
00:06:33.361 --> 00:06:35.863
What about your book?
You were a stocking stuffer.

172
00:06:35.997 --> 00:06:38.232
And again. that's great.
but it's not exactly a windfall.

173
00:06:38.366 --> 00:06:40.334
I mean. most authors
also have a day job.

174
00:06:40.467 --> 00:06:41.602
Candi's an author.

175
00:06:41.736 --> 00:06:43.571
It's absolute smut
but well told.

176
00:06:43.704 --> 00:06:45.573
So. wh-what are you saying. Sam?

177
00:06:45.706 --> 00:06:49.844
I'm saying we won't need
Trevor's money. eventually.

178
00:06:49.977 --> 00:06:52.213
But if we want to make it
to summer.

179
00:06:52.346 --> 00:06:54.849
we got to save Trevor's job.

180
00:06:57.318 --> 00:06:59.587
Looks like Michael Jackson
is going to HR.

181
00:07:04.424 --> 00:07:06.160
Let me ask you guys something.

182
00:07:06.227 --> 00:07:09.063
Do you think it's okay for
someone to make a special trip

183
00:07:09.196 --> 00:07:10.932
to see their ex when
they're dating someone else?

184
00:07:11.065 --> 00:07:13.267
It wasn't a special trip.
I was in the neighborhood.

185
00:07:13.401 --> 00:07:15.435
Is Saint Lucia in the
neighborhood. though?

186
00:07:15.569 --> 00:07:17.071
I'm not a geography expert.

187
00:07:17.204 --> 00:07:18.873
but I feel like
you have to go out of your way.

188
00:07:19.006 --> 00:07:20.942
Well. you know. the Caribbean
isn't that big of a place.

189
00:07:21.075 --> 00:07:23.945
Caribbean Islands span over
thousand miles east to west.

190
00:07:24.078 --> 00:07:25.780
You know that because of
your Viking voyages?

191
00:07:25.913 --> 00:07:27.214
No.

192
00:07:27.348 --> 00:07:29.550
Captain Sandy sailed ship
out of Antigua.

193
00:07:29.684 --> 00:07:31.385
season eight. <i>Below Deck.</i>

194
00:07:31.552 --> 00:07:34.288
Reality TV is a fount of wisdom.
It doesn't get enough credit.

195
00:07:34.422 --> 00:07:36.290
Donna and I are just friends.

196
00:07:36.424 --> 00:07:38.059
It's still weird.
She might be into you.

197
00:07:38.192 --> 00:07:40.460
But I'm not into her.
so it doesn't matter.

198
00:07:40.594 --> 00:07:43.297
Okay. well. that
British shed ghost Baxter and I

199
00:07:43.431 --> 00:07:45.132
had a thing back in '29.

200
00:07:45.266 --> 00:07:47.568
Would it bother you
if he and I started hanging out?

201
00:07:47.702 --> 00:07:49.236
As friends. of course.

202
00:07:49.370 --> 00:07:50.938
I was there when they met.

203
00:07:51.072 --> 00:07:52.740
It was love at first fife.

204
00:07:52.873 --> 00:07:55.142
Actually. "love" is
a bit of an overstatement.

205
00:07:55.276 --> 00:07:57.278
I needed it
for the turn of phrase.

206
00:07:58.279 --> 00:07:59.847
You know what?

207
00:07:59.981 --> 00:08:01.615
I-I think if you wanted
to catch up with your ex Baxter.

208
00:08:01.749 --> 00:08:02.917
I would be fine with it.

209
00:08:03.050 --> 00:08:04.518
Okay.

210
00:08:04.652 --> 00:08:06.654
"Okay." like we're good
and that's the end of it?

211
00:08:06.787 --> 00:08:08.488
Yep.

212
00:08:11.959 --> 00:08:14.261
Thor not think
that the end of it.

213
00:08:16.297 --> 00:08:18.833
Okay. Trevor is gonna give you
a crash course

214
00:08:18.966 --> 00:08:21.168
in everything you need to know
about your character:

215
00:08:21.302 --> 00:08:23.671
Michael Jackson.
financial analyst.

216
00:08:23.804 --> 00:08:25.306
What the hell is my life?

217
00:08:25.439 --> 00:08:28.142
Born on the outskirts
of the Motor City...

218
00:08:28.275 --> 00:08:29.677
I don't think we have time

219
00:08:29.810 --> 00:08:31.479
to go through
the entire backstory. Trevor.

220
00:08:31.612 --> 00:08:33.180
Yeah. maybe just give me
the must-knows.

221
00:08:33.314 --> 00:08:34.648
Okay.

222
00:08:34.782 --> 00:08:36.951
First of all.
there's a major flirtation

223
00:08:37.084 --> 00:08:38.486
with my coworker Maggie.

224
00:08:38.652 --> 00:08:41.022
who you know from
the work retreat we had here.

225
00:08:41.155 --> 00:08:43.724
So. there's a flirtatious thing
going on with Maggie.

226
00:08:43.858 --> 00:08:45.526
But he says
to keep it respectful.

227
00:08:45.659 --> 00:08:47.061
No. I didn't.

228
00:08:47.194 --> 00:08:49.563
Trust me. Maggie does not
appreciate respectful.

229
00:08:49.697 --> 00:08:50.898
Wait. time-out. Sam.

230
00:08:51.032 --> 00:08:52.533
Why do I need to know
any of this?

231
00:08:52.666 --> 00:08:55.803
I'm just going to ask HR
to forgive Michael Jackson

232
00:08:55.936 --> 00:08:57.872
for sending his boss
a stripper-gram.

233
00:08:58.005 --> 00:09:00.641
Okay. but you're going
into the lion's den. baby.

234
00:09:00.775 --> 00:09:02.843
You have no idea
who you're gonna meet.

235
00:09:02.977 --> 00:09:04.545
and you need to be prepared.

236
00:09:04.678 --> 00:09:05.846
Also. can you find out
what happened

237
00:09:05.980 --> 00:09:07.048
with Candi and the HVAC?

238
00:09:07.181 --> 00:09:09.016
I am dying to know.

239
00:09:09.150 --> 00:09:10.217
He says that
you just need to be ready.

240
00:09:10.351 --> 00:09:12.219
in case you run into anybody.

241
00:09:12.353 --> 00:09:13.821
Okay. Continue.

242
00:09:13.954 --> 00:09:16.390
So. if he runs into
anybody on my team.

243
00:09:16.525 --> 00:09:18.659
this is definitely
gonna come up.

244
00:09:20.529 --> 00:09:22.329
Okay.

245
00:09:22.463 --> 00:09:24.198
Michael Jackson is
currently closing a deal

246
00:09:24.331 --> 00:09:26.167
for the McDaniels Corporation.
who makes soap.

247
00:09:26.300 --> 00:09:28.736
to acquire the McCallister
Corporation. who makes sponges.

248
00:09:28.869 --> 00:09:30.905
Now. McDaniels is
offering 30 million.

249
00:09:31.038 --> 00:09:32.406
but McCallister wants 40.

250
00:09:32.541 --> 00:09:34.241
but Trevor thinks
you'll close at 35

251
00:09:34.375 --> 00:09:37.078
and then celebrate
at Peter Luger's with the CEOs.

252
00:09:37.211 --> 00:09:39.880
Conan McDaniels
and Galen McCallister.

253
00:09:40.014 --> 00:09:42.249
Sam. I'm not gonna remember
any of that.

254
00:09:42.383 --> 00:09:43.751
Also. I told them
I could moonwalk.

255
00:09:43.884 --> 00:09:45.753
so make sure
Jay is prepared for that.

256
00:09:45.886 --> 00:09:47.588
-Seriously?
-What?

257
00:09:47.721 --> 00:09:49.857
How are your moonwalking skills?

258
00:09:49.990 --> 00:09:52.259
Not good. Sam.

259
00:09:52.393 --> 00:09:54.395
Not good!

260
00:09:54.563 --> 00:09:56.230
<i>Well. it is really good</i>

261
00:09:56.363 --> 00:09:57.765
to catch up with you. Baxter.

262
00:09:59.400 --> 00:10:01.769
Hey. guys.
What's. uh. going on in here?

263
00:10:01.902 --> 00:10:04.905
Oh. just hanging out
with a friend.

264
00:10:05.039 --> 00:10:06.207
doing a little catching up.

265
00:10:06.340 --> 00:10:07.708
-You okay with that?
-Of course.

266
00:10:07.842 --> 00:10:09.443
Yeah. two friends catching up.

267
00:10:09.578 --> 00:10:11.712
What could be more wholesome
or totally okay than that?

268
00:10:11.846 --> 00:10:15.082
It's just. we have so much
in common. Alberta and I.

269
00:10:15.216 --> 00:10:17.618
For instance.
the whole music thing.

270
00:10:17.751 --> 00:10:19.120
Right.

271
00:10:19.253 --> 00:10:20.788
You know. I played
a mean oboe in my day.

272
00:10:20.921 --> 00:10:23.558
That's nice. although I died
with my instrument.

273
00:10:23.691 --> 00:10:26.460
-so it's sort of
a different kettle of fish.
-Mm.

274
00:10:26.595 --> 00:10:28.729
Well. good for you.

275
00:10:28.863 --> 00:10:32.466
Ha! You remind me
of my flatmate Jenkins.

276
00:10:32.601 --> 00:10:34.635
He's always saying that.

277
00:10:34.768 --> 00:10:35.769
"Goody for you."

278
00:10:35.903 --> 00:10:37.972
Oh. my God!

279
00:10:38.105 --> 00:10:40.641
You do
the best Jenkins impression.

280
00:10:40.774 --> 00:10:42.776
How was that an impression?

281
00:10:42.910 --> 00:10:44.979
They're both just British.
He barely changed his voice.

282
00:10:45.112 --> 00:10:46.814
This is an impression:

283
00:10:46.947 --> 00:10:48.983
"I am not a crook."

284
00:10:49.116 --> 00:10:50.951
Oh. Is that Trevor?

285
00:10:51.085 --> 00:10:52.253
No. it's Nixon.

286
00:10:52.386 --> 00:10:53.821
Here's one for you:

287
00:10:53.954 --> 00:10:56.123
"How 'bout we all pop out
to the shed?"

288
00:10:56.257 --> 00:10:57.791
- Nigel! Classic!
- Ha!

289
00:10:57.925 --> 00:10:59.193
In one. Well done.

290
00:10:59.326 --> 00:11:00.828
It's not--
Th-They all sound the same!

291
00:11:00.961 --> 00:11:02.963
Are you all right. Peter?

292
00:11:03.097 --> 00:11:04.965
No! I'm not all right.

293
00:11:05.099 --> 00:11:07.001
This is my girl.
and if she's gonna be laughing

294
00:11:07.134 --> 00:11:08.769
at any impressions.
they're gonna be mine!

295
00:11:08.903 --> 00:11:11.172
Oh. my. I'm deeply sorry.

296
00:11:11.305 --> 00:11:13.007
You know what?

297
00:11:13.140 --> 00:11:15.276
Go fife yourself!

298
00:11:16.243 --> 00:11:17.978
<i>I'm sorry that you had to do</i>

299
00:11:18.112 --> 00:11:20.681
this whole. uh.
"come in and talk to HR" thing.

300
00:11:20.814 --> 00:11:22.950
I mean. honestly. I thought
the stripper-gram rocked.

301
00:11:23.083 --> 00:11:25.352
Oh. well. that's very kind
of you. Brettinator.

302
00:11:25.486 --> 00:11:27.054
No. seriously.

303
00:11:27.188 --> 00:11:28.856
no one has the balls to send
a real present anymore.

304
00:11:28.989 --> 00:11:30.858
Hey. so how about McCallister

305
00:11:30.991 --> 00:11:32.661
-with that counter?
-Oh. yeah.

306
00:11:32.793 --> 00:11:34.663
Be honest. what do you think
about that termination fee?

307
00:11:34.795 --> 00:11:37.632
Oh. it was brutal.

308
00:11:38.633 --> 00:11:42.537
Or good. depending on if you are
McCallister or McDaniels.

309
00:11:42.671 --> 00:11:44.673
vis-à-vis the counter.

310
00:11:46.273 --> 00:11:48.709
Hey. you-you guys
want to see me moonwalk?

311
00:11:48.842 --> 00:11:50.545
Uh... hell yeah. we do!

312
00:11:50.679 --> 00:11:51.745
Okay.

313
00:11:51.879 --> 00:11:53.548
Thought you'd never ask.

314
00:11:53.682 --> 00:11:55.482
Ooh!

315
00:11:55.617 --> 00:11:57.552
-Ooh!
-Oh!

316
00:11:57.686 --> 00:12:00.187
You're the smooth criminal. MJ.

317
00:12:00.321 --> 00:12:02.423
Ow! ...are you doing?

318
00:12:02.557 --> 00:12:04.725
I am Michael Jackson.

319
00:12:04.858 --> 00:12:06.561
Anthony Valerie from HR.

320
00:12:06.695 --> 00:12:09.263
Okay. so we'll just
leave you guys to it.

321
00:12:09.396 --> 00:12:11.498
Good luck. MJ.

322
00:12:12.499 --> 00:12:14.235
Thank you for coming in.
Mr. Jackson.

323
00:12:14.368 --> 00:12:15.604
Oh. no. no. it's no problem.

324
00:12:15.736 --> 00:12:17.238
And I just want to say
right off the bat

325
00:12:17.371 --> 00:12:19.240
that I know that the
stripper-gram was in poor taste.

326
00:12:19.373 --> 00:12:20.841
and it'll never happen again.

327
00:12:20.975 --> 00:12:22.577
Here's the thing.

328
00:12:22.711 --> 00:12:24.912
Once we started interviewing
people about the incident.

329
00:12:25.045 --> 00:12:26.947
other complaints emerged
regarding your time here.

330
00:12:30.050 --> 00:12:32.753
Take a seat. Mr. Jackson.
We have a lot to talk about.

331
00:12:37.559 --> 00:12:40.695
October 4th. while referencing
a new Slack headshot

332
00:12:40.828 --> 00:12:43.030
of a female coworker.
you commented.

333
00:12:43.163 --> 00:12:45.099
"Giggity. giggity. giggity."

334
00:12:45.232 --> 00:12:47.901
Which a quick Google search
reveals to be

335
00:12:48.035 --> 00:12:50.538
the horny catchphrase of
a popular animated pervert.

336
00:12:50.672 --> 00:12:54.108
Yeah. I was unaware
of that phrase's origins.

337
00:12:54.241 --> 00:12:56.477
and I deeply apologize for that.

338
00:12:56.611 --> 00:12:58.279
October 10th.

339
00:12:58.412 --> 00:13:01.215
You asked your entire team
to. quote. "send nudes."

340
00:13:01.348 --> 00:13:04.285
You know. I think I-I meant
to type. um. "send news."

341
00:13:04.418 --> 00:13:06.186
You know.
I'm a huge news buff.

342
00:13:06.320 --> 00:13:09.290
but I'm also so busy that
I don't have time to locate it.

343
00:13:09.423 --> 00:13:11.292
It's a difficult combination.

344
00:13:11.425 --> 00:13:12.993
Look. I get it--
boys will be boys.

345
00:13:13.127 --> 00:13:14.596
and this is
the finance industry.

346
00:13:14.729 --> 00:13:16.830
but it's not the '90s.

347
00:13:16.964 --> 00:13:18.633
People don't act
this way anymore.

348
00:13:18.767 --> 00:13:20.434
You're right.

349
00:13:20.568 --> 00:13:23.103
I joined this industry at a time
when things were different.

350
00:13:23.237 --> 00:13:24.805
and-and I've had
trouble adjusting.

351
00:13:24.938 --> 00:13:26.807
but I am committed
to correcting my behavior.

352
00:13:26.940 --> 00:13:28.976
My mother raised
a better man than this.

353
00:13:29.943 --> 00:13:31.945
I hear that.

354
00:13:32.079 --> 00:13:34.315
We're all just out here trying
to make our moms proud. right?

355
00:13:34.448 --> 00:13:36.817
Right? My mom always says.

356
00:13:36.950 --> 00:13:38.852
"You can't make
a perfect khichdi.

357
00:13:38.986 --> 00:13:41.656
You just have to keep tasting it
and trying to make it better."

358
00:13:41.790 --> 00:13:43.658
And that is how I treat my life.

359
00:13:43.792 --> 00:13:45.794
Yeah. That's really good.

360
00:13:45.926 --> 00:13:47.995
And kind of familiar.
Where have I heard that before?

361
00:13:48.128 --> 00:13:49.764
I-I just came up with it.

362
00:13:49.897 --> 00:13:50.998
No. it's
a pretty specific anecdote.

363
00:13:51.131 --> 00:13:52.199
and I remember hearing it.

364
00:13:52.333 --> 00:13:53.735
Uh. wait.

365
00:13:53.901 --> 00:13:56.837
Have you ever listened
to <i>The Todd Pod?</i>

366
00:13:56.970 --> 00:13:59.139
I'm not sure.

367
00:13:59.273 --> 00:14:02.343
Huh. this chef said the
exact thing that you just said.

368
00:14:02.476 --> 00:14:05.312
Yep. here it is.
Chef Jay Arondekar.

369
00:14:06.313 --> 00:14:07.348
Wait a second.

370
00:14:07.481 --> 00:14:09.016
This is clearly you.

371
00:14:09.149 --> 00:14:10.851
No. not clearly.

372
00:14:10.984 --> 00:14:13.220
What the hell is going on.
Mr. Arondekar?

373
00:14:14.188 --> 00:14:17.358
Um... you want
to see me moonwalk?

374
00:14:18.459 --> 00:14:20.494
Well. I got fired.
Or Trevor got fired.

375
00:14:20.628 --> 00:14:22.196
Michael Jackson got fired?
I don't know.

376
00:14:22.329 --> 00:14:24.532
-We're fired.
-Seriously? What happened?

377
00:14:24.666 --> 00:14:26.467
You couldn't get Trevor
off the hook?

378
00:14:26.601 --> 00:14:27.669
No. I managed that all
pretty well.

379
00:14:27.802 --> 00:14:29.136
It wasn't easy.

380
00:14:29.269 --> 00:14:30.739
This guy's got a lot
of complaints about him.

381
00:14:30.871 --> 00:14:31.972
Given the speed
at which you type.

382
00:14:32.106 --> 00:14:33.474
it's actually impressive

383
00:14:33.608 --> 00:14:35.376
how prolifically problematic
you manage to be.

384
00:14:35.510 --> 00:14:37.579
But then the HR guy
recognized me

385
00:14:37.746 --> 00:14:39.880
from our appearance
on <i>The Todd Pod.</i>

386
00:14:40.013 --> 00:14:42.015
Creepy Todd strikes again.

387
00:14:42.149 --> 00:14:43.984
He was willing to overlook
some light sexual harassment.

388
00:14:44.118 --> 00:14:46.353
but he drew the line
at identity fraud.

389
00:14:46.487 --> 00:14:48.523
So that's it. I'm fired.

390
00:14:48.656 --> 00:14:50.891
Security carried me out
mid-moonwalk.

391
00:14:51.024 --> 00:14:52.660
It was humiliating.

392
00:14:52.794 --> 00:14:55.195
Well. this day has taken a turn.

393
00:14:55.329 --> 00:14:58.165
Michael Jackson's good name
dragged through the mud.

394
00:14:58.298 --> 00:14:59.567
I'm sorry. Jay.

395
00:14:59.701 --> 00:15:00.735
I shouldn't have put you
in that situation.

396
00:15:00.869 --> 00:15:02.336
It's not just that.

397
00:15:02.469 --> 00:15:03.937
You lied to me.

398
00:15:04.071 --> 00:15:05.906
There shouldn't be
financial consequences for us

399
00:15:06.039 --> 00:15:07.509
if a ghost loses their job.

400
00:15:07.642 --> 00:15:09.076
Why didn't you just tell me
what was going on?

401
00:15:09.209 --> 00:15:10.578
I was just trying
to protect you.

402
00:15:10.712 --> 00:15:12.246
I didn't want you to worry.

403
00:15:12.379 --> 00:15:14.047
I don't need protecting.

404
00:15:14.181 --> 00:15:15.550
He's right. Sam.

405
00:15:15.683 --> 00:15:17.384
You don't hide secrets like that
from your spouse.

406
00:15:17.519 --> 00:15:20.120
Didn't you keep kind of
a whopper from Beatrice?

407
00:15:20.254 --> 00:15:22.423
The truth is.
I wasn't just protecting you.

408
00:15:22.557 --> 00:15:25.426
I... I was also
protecting myself.

409
00:15:25.560 --> 00:15:27.194
Oh. what does that
even mean. Sam?

410
00:15:27.327 --> 00:15:30.097
I was embarrassed. okay?

411
00:15:30.230 --> 00:15:32.099
You've made so much progress
on the restaurant.

412
00:15:32.232 --> 00:15:33.535
and it's only been a year.

413
00:15:33.668 --> 00:15:35.235
Meanwhile. on my side of things.

414
00:15:35.369 --> 00:15:38.105
we're five years in. and
the B and B is still struggling.

415
00:15:38.238 --> 00:15:40.274
Yeah. you're mad at me.

416
00:15:40.407 --> 00:15:42.877
Well. I get it.
That makes two of us.

417
00:15:48.550 --> 00:15:50.785
-So...
-So?

418
00:15:51.853 --> 00:15:54.923
I think it's possible
that you were right.

419
00:15:55.055 --> 00:15:56.089
A little louder.

420
00:15:56.223 --> 00:15:57.257
You were right.

421
00:15:57.391 --> 00:15:59.393
It bugged me.

422
00:15:59.527 --> 00:16:01.596
Even though I know you're not
gonna do anything with Baxter.

423
00:16:01.729 --> 00:16:02.931
You aren't. are you?

424
00:16:03.063 --> 00:16:04.097
No.

425
00:16:04.231 --> 00:16:06.433
Okay. good.

426
00:16:06.568 --> 00:16:09.970
Look. neither of us
did anything technically wrong

427
00:16:10.103 --> 00:16:12.306
spending time
with Donna or Baxter.

428
00:16:12.439 --> 00:16:14.274
but when you're in
a relationship. you have to

429
00:16:14.408 --> 00:16:16.143
consider how it's gonna make
the other person feel.

430
00:16:16.276 --> 00:16:17.978
I-I get that now. I do.

431
00:16:18.111 --> 00:16:20.949
And don't worry.
I won't go to Saint Lucia again.

432
00:16:21.081 --> 00:16:22.149
Thank you. Pete.

433
00:16:22.282 --> 00:16:23.350
Or Stockholm.

434
00:16:23.484 --> 00:16:24.985
Or Banff. Or Denver.

435
00:16:25.118 --> 00:16:26.855
-Pete.
-Sorry.

436
00:16:26.987 --> 00:16:29.456
I went on a bit of a tear when
I first discovered I could roam.

437
00:16:29.591 --> 00:16:30.925
This was way before
we were together.

438
00:16:31.058 --> 00:16:32.627
It's just kind of like.
everywhere I go.

439
00:16:32.760 --> 00:16:34.762
I'm the new ghost.
and you know how that is.

440
00:16:34.896 --> 00:16:36.330
-Oh. my God.
-But here's the thing.

441
00:16:36.463 --> 00:16:38.499
Yes. I can go
anywhere in the world.

442
00:16:38.633 --> 00:16:41.669
but there's nowhere I'd rather
be than right here with you.

443
00:16:41.803 --> 00:16:43.538
Oh. Pete.

444
00:16:46.473 --> 00:16:49.109
Hey. y-you didn't really think

445
00:16:49.243 --> 00:16:51.513
any of Baxter's impressions
were good. did you?

446
00:16:51.646 --> 00:16:53.781
Let it go.

447
00:16:53.915 --> 00:16:55.315
It just gets me steamed.

448
00:16:55.449 --> 00:16:58.553
I mean. it's an art form!
You got to respect it!

449
00:16:59.988 --> 00:17:01.723
Sam. I just want to apologize.

450
00:17:01.856 --> 00:17:03.992
I know I put you
in a really tough spot.

451
00:17:04.124 --> 00:17:06.528
I just wish that there was
something that I could do.

452
00:17:06.661 --> 00:17:08.796
Don't worry about it.
You were just trying to help.

453
00:17:08.930 --> 00:17:12.232
I shouldn't be in a position
where I needed your help.

454
00:17:12.366 --> 00:17:14.368
It's my fault
I can't run my own business.

455
00:17:14.502 --> 00:17:16.403
Look. Samantha.
I know you're struggling.

456
00:17:16.538 --> 00:17:18.405
but you're gonna
figure this out.

457
00:17:18.540 --> 00:17:19.874
We believe in you.

458
00:17:20.008 --> 00:17:21.375
And when you do.

459
00:17:21.509 --> 00:17:23.210
I think you're gonna
look back at this time

460
00:17:23.343 --> 00:17:24.712
with a lot of fondness.

461
00:17:24.846 --> 00:17:25.713
What do you mean?

462
00:17:25.847 --> 00:17:27.515
This time. right now.

463
00:17:27.649 --> 00:17:29.717
while you're grinding it out

464
00:17:29.851 --> 00:17:32.820
and-and living
in that uncertainty.

465
00:17:32.954 --> 00:17:35.188
I know it doesn't feel like it.
but that's the good stuff.

466
00:17:35.322 --> 00:17:36.323
He's right.

467
00:17:36.456 --> 00:17:37.892
Having a goal. having a purpose.

468
00:17:38.026 --> 00:17:39.694
like. that's such
a big part of life.

469
00:17:39.827 --> 00:17:41.896
And I miss that.

470
00:17:42.030 --> 00:17:43.932
Also eating.
That was good.

471
00:17:45.465 --> 00:17:47.401
Many times.
so-called "overnight success"

472
00:17:47.535 --> 00:17:50.237
only come after
years of failure.

473
00:17:50.370 --> 00:17:52.372
That's true. He's right. Sam.

474
00:17:52.507 --> 00:17:56.044
This actually embarrassing
for Thor to admit.

475
00:17:56.176 --> 00:17:57.912
but early in Thor's career.

476
00:17:58.046 --> 00:18:01.749
I struggle to even kill
just one Dane.

477
00:18:01.883 --> 00:18:04.619
But then Thor turn 13.

478
00:18:04.752 --> 00:18:06.621
and blood run like river.

479
00:18:06.754 --> 00:18:09.256
I guess tangentially
that's what we're saying.

480
00:18:10.223 --> 00:18:11.593
Thanks. guys.

481
00:18:11.726 --> 00:18:13.460
Oh. hey. babe.

482
00:18:13.595 --> 00:18:15.429
I was thinking about
what you said before.

483
00:18:15.563 --> 00:18:17.765
and I just want you to know

484
00:18:17.899 --> 00:18:21.268
that there is
no your thing or my thing.

485
00:18:21.401 --> 00:18:23.771
It's all our thing.

486
00:18:26.173 --> 00:18:27.775
He is a keeper.

487
00:18:27.909 --> 00:18:31.913
These kind words
will surely reap kind acts.

488
00:18:32.046 --> 00:18:33.447
Sex. I mean.

489
00:18:33.581 --> 00:18:34.816
There are no sides.

490
00:18:34.949 --> 00:18:37.451
We win as a team.
and we lose as a team.

491
00:18:37.585 --> 00:18:39.721
Besides. there wouldn't be
a restaurant without you.

492
00:18:39.854 --> 00:18:41.388
It was your idea.

493
00:18:41.522 --> 00:18:42.957
I guess it was. huh?

494
00:18:43.091 --> 00:18:44.324
I mean. it was right there.

495
00:18:44.458 --> 00:18:46.426
It wasn't like
she invented calculus.

496
00:18:46.561 --> 00:18:48.596
And we're making real strides
with the B and B.

497
00:18:48.730 --> 00:18:51.264
We got on that prestigious list
of small hotels.

498
00:18:51.398 --> 00:18:53.801
Thanks to the fact the list guy
was a huge cocaine fiend.

499
00:18:53.935 --> 00:18:57.105
And now our bookings are up.

500
00:18:57.237 --> 00:18:59.239
I mean. we're about to
turn a corner. I can feel it.

501
00:18:59.373 --> 00:19:01.809
You know. some of the ghosts
were saying

502
00:19:01.943 --> 00:19:03.778
we're actually gonna look back
on this time.

503
00:19:03.911 --> 00:19:06.648
on-on the struggle.
and we're gonna miss it.

504
00:19:06.781 --> 00:19:08.750
Sometimes they can be
pretty wise.

505
00:19:08.883 --> 00:19:10.818
I recall one evening.

506
00:19:10.952 --> 00:19:14.187
our wine steward dropped dead
right before a dinner party.

507
00:19:14.321 --> 00:19:19.426
so I was forced to wield
the corkscrew myself.

508
00:19:19.560 --> 00:19:24.132
In many ways. it was the
sweetest wine I've ever tasted.

509
00:19:24.264 --> 00:19:26.466
Some of them struggled
more than others.

510
00:19:31.171 --> 00:19:33.841
Am I crazy or is it. whenever
you're worried about money.

511
00:19:33.975 --> 00:19:35.643
that suddenly
a bunch of bills show up?

512
00:19:35.777 --> 00:19:38.345
No. we can keep complaining
or we can tighten our belts

513
00:19:38.478 --> 00:19:40.447
and do something about it.

514
00:19:40.581 --> 00:19:42.050
Look. you guys are resourceful.

515
00:19:42.182 --> 00:19:43.518
You'll find a way to hustle up
some extra income.

516
00:19:43.651 --> 00:19:45.318
Pete's right.

517
00:19:45.452 --> 00:19:47.187
Your feet are one pumice stone
away from being Web-ready.

518
00:19:47.320 --> 00:19:49.524
Okay. I meant like a bake sale.
My God. Trevor.

519
00:19:49.657 --> 00:19:52.694
Okay. I appreciate everyone's
ideas. but we will handle this.

520
00:19:52.827 --> 00:19:54.327
We're gonna be fine.

521
00:19:54.461 --> 00:19:55.997
Babe. this is
a letter from the IRS.

522
00:19:56.130 --> 00:19:59.466
Apparently. I'm being
investigated for tax evasion

523
00:19:59.600 --> 00:20:04.038
because Michael Jackson hasn't
paid any taxes for two years!

524
00:20:04.172 --> 00:20:06.206
What? Trevor. you didn't
pay your taxes?

525
00:20:06.339 --> 00:20:08.375
I'm a ghost! I don't use
any government services.

526
00:20:08.509 --> 00:20:10.044
Also. Isaac told me
I didn't have to.

527
00:20:10.178 --> 00:20:11.913
He said it was taxation
without representation.

528
00:20:12.046 --> 00:20:14.549
Yes. Sam. please tell Jay
that his nonpayment

529
00:20:14.682 --> 00:20:17.051
stands on
firm philosophical grounds.

530
00:20:17.185 --> 00:20:19.887
We are so screwed!

531
00:20:20.021 --> 00:20:22.255
Uh. where exactly is Trevor
in the room?

532
00:20:22.389 --> 00:20:24.092
He's on the couch.
on my other side.

533
00:20:24.224 --> 00:20:27.327
Good. I want to make sure
I address this directly to him.

534
00:20:29.197 --> 00:20:33.034
Trevor. I forgive you.

535
00:20:33.167 --> 00:20:34.367
Ah.

536
00:20:34.502 --> 00:20:36.070
Right after I do this.
